WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:01.920
- I saw a video the other day.

00:00:01.920 --> 00:00:04.980
It was sent to me by a
bunch of X three fans

00:00:04.980 --> 00:00:08.610
and the title of the video
was, you Can't Get Big

00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:09.720
with Bands.

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:12.420
And they expected me to be
offended, respond to 'em.

00:00:12.420 --> 00:00:16.650
And I said, yeah, this, this
video's correct. Bands suck.

00:00:16.650 --> 00:00:18.780
And they were like,
but what about X three?

00:00:18.780 --> 00:00:23.070
Well, X three uses bands so

00:00:23.070 --> 00:00:26.520
that we load the bottom of the exercise

00:00:26.520 --> 00:00:30.180
and hyper load the top
so we have more access

00:00:30.180 --> 00:00:31.830
to more musculature at the top.

00:00:31.830 --> 00:00:33.720
We first exhaust at the top.

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:35.280
So you're doing repetitions

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:37.620
and you go, you never go to lockout,

00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:39.000
but you go close to lockout.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.820
So you want 120 degree angle
between upper and lower arm.

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:43.830
You're gonna do however
many repetitions you can do

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:45.570
until you can't get there anymore.

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:47.970
And then you just go as far as you can.

00:00:47.970 --> 00:00:51.210
Now if you did this trying
to do like a pushup,

00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:53.820
like you just throw a
band around your back

00:00:53.820 --> 00:00:55.500
and you try to press away from yourself,

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.630
you'd end up twisting your joints.

00:00:57.630 --> 00:01:01.650
You wouldn't get to muscular
stimulus or even fatigue at all

00:01:01.650 --> 00:01:04.020
because you'd have to
stop because of the pain.

00:01:04.020 --> 00:01:06.150
So that's a process
called neural inhibition.

00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:12.440
So bands by themselves,
not even worth training.

00:01:12.870 --> 00:01:14.670
Like if all you have access

00:01:14.670 --> 00:01:16.620
to is bands don't even work out with 'em.

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:18.960
I'd rather you lift weights.

00:01:18.960 --> 00:01:21.060
And I wrote the book,
weightlifting is a waste of time.

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:22.350
That's not very effective either,

00:01:22.350 --> 00:01:25.020
but it's better than the joint
damage you're gonna receive

00:01:25.020 --> 00:01:27.540
from trying to train just with bands.

00:01:27.540 --> 00:01:30.900
If you have the rest of
the apparatus, the bar

00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:34.590
that keeps your wrist
neutral as you're pushing

00:01:34.590 --> 00:01:36.000
and pulling, that's key.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:39.720
And then also the platform that
the banding runs underneath

00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:41.190
that the X three has.

00:01:41.190 --> 00:01:43.800
That's super important too,
because if you stand on a band,

00:01:43.800 --> 00:01:45.510
and let's say you're
trying to do a deadlift,

00:01:45.510 --> 00:01:48.780
keep in mind it only takes
seven pounds of lateral force

00:01:48.780 --> 00:01:49.980
to break the human ankle.

00:01:49.980 --> 00:01:54.480
Well, when I use X three,
I'm deadlifting 700 pounds.

00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:56.010
So what do you think that's gonna do?

00:01:56.010 --> 00:01:58.800
If I just step on the band and try

00:01:58.800 --> 00:02:03.600
and put 700 lateral pounds
through my ankle joint?

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:06.330
Lateral means this way, not this way.

00:02:06.330 --> 00:02:09.150
I'd probably break an ankle or both.

00:02:09.150 --> 00:02:12.540
So now the good news is
your central nervous system

00:02:12.540 --> 00:02:13.590
will just protect you.

00:02:13.590 --> 00:02:16.560
So if you try and do that,
you just won't be able to

00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:17.730
like your central nervous system

00:02:17.730 --> 00:02:19.590
through a process called
neural inhibition,

00:02:19.590 --> 00:02:21.060
which has shut you down.

00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:22.950
So bands

00:02:22.950 --> 00:02:27.480
by themselves totally suck X three may

00:02:27.480 --> 00:02:30.870
bands very usable, very portable.

00:02:30.870 --> 00:02:33.540
And the most important thing,

00:02:33.540 --> 00:02:35.520
and I know a lot of
people think I don't agree

00:02:35.520 --> 00:02:38.520
with this whole like
stretch range of motion

00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:40.110
or lengthened range of motion,

00:02:40.110 --> 00:02:44.220
that's the only place muscle
stimulus ever took place.

00:02:44.220 --> 00:02:48.240
Like it's not that that range
of motion is special, it's

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:50.790
that you have less muscle capable

00:02:50.790 --> 00:02:52.500
of firing in those positions.

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:54.210
So that's where you go to fatigue.

00:02:54.210 --> 00:02:56.550
That's where you show the
central nervous system, Hey,

00:02:56.550 --> 00:02:59.820
we don't have enough muscle
here and we can add more.

00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:04.170
So you never want to not
load the bottom, you have

00:03:04.170 --> 00:03:08.760
to load the bottom, and it takes
other equipment to do that.

00:03:08.760 --> 00:03:10.890
A band by itself, you'll fail every time.

